 :tx/rationale "CORR-1: LIVE view ignores bare retractions and hardcodes LWW for ALL attributes [CRITICAL, from FULL_AUDIT F-INV-001 + AUDIT_REPORT F-CORR-002]. Two related defects in store.rs index_datom(): (1) Retraction ordering: the LIVE view uses live_view.remove() which only works if retracted value matches current LIVE value. If retraction arrives before assertion (possible in CRDT merge), LIVE view wont reflect it when assertion later arrives. The from_datoms() rebuild processes in BTreeSet order (entity,attr,value,tx,op) not causal (tx) order, so assert-before-retract is not guaranteed. (2) LWW hardcoded: index_datom() at store.rs:1089-1100 applies last-writer-wins regardless of schema-declared resolution mode. Multi-cardinality attributes silently lose all but latest value. store.live_value() returns incorrect results for non-LWW attributes. INV-STORE-012 violated. SOLUTION: (1) LIVE rebuild must process datoms in causal (tx) order, not BTreeSet order. Incremental path must check retracted value matches current LIVE before removing. (2) Route LIVE view updates through schema.resolution_mode(attr) — Multi-cardinality keeps all values, Lattice applies join. VERIFICATION: Proptest with 10K random assert/retract sequences in random order, verify LIVE matches fold-based computation over causally-sorted datoms. Unit test for Multi-cardinality attribute retaining multiple values. DEPENDENCIES: Blocks correct F(S) computation (bilateral reads LIVE). Blocks AUDIT-SOUND-1 (coherence gate should check against correct LIVE state). Interacts with AUDIT-PERF-2 (merge rebuild should use corrected LIVE logic)."
